    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-17T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-17T11:00:00-05:00" n="857"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d857">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111 A.R.–Subs/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-17T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 17, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>65. Department’s circular June 13, 8 p.m. Secretary of State said that he would
                    add to Cuba’s neutrality legislation a provision excluding belligerent
                    submarines from Cuban ports and territorial waters similar to that contained in
                    the proclamation of the President of the United States of November 4, 1939.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Messersmith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
